The paper deals with the problem of discovering the skyline of web databases, which involves ranking and selecting the top tuples based on a proprietary ranking function. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including databases (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and web technologies (cs.WEB). Given the focus on web databases and search interfaces, cs.WEB is also a likely category. However, since the paper proposes algorithms and provides theoretical analysis, cs.DS and cs.AI are also plausible categories. Overall, cs.DB and cs.IR are the most likely categories, followed by cs.DS, cs.AI, and cs.WEB.
